race.comment: The $250,000 Class 6 Plate closes out the card. ROSELYN'S STAR (14) resumes here but the form she showed when last in work was good enough to warrant serious consideration in a race of this calibre. Revved up for this with two strong NSW trials and a strong showing while fresh would not shock. HAWKER HALL (12) is a consistent conveyance who has only missed the top-five once in ten career starts. Ready to peak now fourth run back and must be respected from the Lees stable. Rates a leading contender. ZOUBABY (16) has finished runner-up at the past couple and looks to be on the doorstep of another victory. Makes some appeal despite the wide draw. JOHN RAMBO (5) saves his best form for this six-furlong trip and doesn't know how to run a bad race. A must for the exotics players. SER JOH (6) next in line.
